  <table class="epi-table25">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <h2></h2>

          <h2>
            <b>SNAP-ChIP<sup>®</sup> as a tool for antibody validation</b>
          </h2>

          <p>
            SNAP-ChIP<sup>®</sup> uses DNA-barcoded recombinant designer
            nucleosomes (dNucs) as next-generation <i>spike-ins</i> for ChIP
            (Right Figure). This technology enables the identification of
            high-quality antibodies by rigorously testing antibody performance
            <u>directly</u> in a ChIP application.
          </p>

          <p>
            In our recent paper published in
            <a
              href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1097276518306750?via%3Dihub "
              >Molecular Cell</a
            >, we applied SNAP-ChIP to directly address the antibody
            reproducibility crisis.
          </p>

          <p>
            <b
              >Conclusion: many commercial 'ChIP-grade' antibodies fail to
              perform as advertised.</b
            >
          </p>

          <p>
            Please contact us for more information about SNAP-ChIP at
            <a href="mailto:info@epicypher.com"><u>info@epicypher.com</u></a>
          </p>

          <p></p>
